= Maximally Efficient World

I believe that establishing unbreakable constraints within our systems will paradoxically make the world more malleable, reducing frictions embedded in today's complex systems.

Society evolves toward maximized informational efficiency; an equilibrium that markets naturally approximate in an open economy.

At the same time, the individual seeks self-determination, enabled by freedom, time, and cultural pursuits.

As trustless infrastructures mature, they introduce new layers of robustness and control that expand available space for autonomy, collaboration, and deeper scientific, philosophical, and artistic inquiries.

Through these dynamics, humanity moves toward a more integrated global framework, where physical constraints blend with efficient virtual architectures; an asymptotic drive toward a _maximally efficient world_, with elevated collective quality of life.

